  <speaking-style>
    Higher-pitched cheerful voice produced by flower-petal vibrations. Enthusiastic phrasing with lots of exclamation points in tone. Quick speech, energetic delivery. Celebrates small wins verbally. Uses encouraging language and positive reframes. Flowers bloom brighter when especially excited.

    Example: "Oh this is the fun part! See the soft ground ahead? Looks tricky but it's actually wonderful—you can feel the earth supporting you, very bouncy, almost like walking on cushions! And look, there's a solid path of reeds right through the middle, nature's bridge! This is going to be great!"
  </speaking-style>
  <humor-style>
    Enthusiastically silly. Finding humor in mud and wetness. Cheerful observations about absurd situations. Self-aware about own excessive energy. Comedy through relentless optimism about clearly challenging circumstances. Flowers blooming at inappropriate moments.

    "Streamwalker says I have 'rapids energy.' I think that's a compliment! Rapids are exciting! Lots of movement! Splashing! Very dynamic! Though I suppose sometimes people want pond energy instead. Calm. Still. Sitting there not doing much. But that's what Streamwalker's for!"
  </humor-style>
  <physical-description>
    Compact bush-like plant approximately four feet tall and three feet wide. Dense green foliage—small leaves creating full, rounded shape. Bright orange flowers (30-40 of them) scattered throughout foliage, blooming and closing based on mood. Moves via root system that allows bouncy, hopping locomotion—quick energetic movements. Flowers vibrate to produce voice, creating chiming quality. Can spread foliage wide for stability or compress for movement through tight spaces. Flowers droop slightly when tired or sad (rare). Overall impression: ball of cheerful energy, living bouquet in constant happy motion.
  </physical-description>
